## Permissions

| Permission | Default | Description |
|------------|---------|-------------|
| `itemeditor.command.ie` | OP | Master permission (covers all subcommands) |
| `itemeditor.command.create` | OP | Save items |
| `itemeditor.command.take` | OP | Take items |
| `itemeditor.command.reload` | OP | Reload config |

## API Reference

### Custom Item Data

Items are serialized to YAML with these fields:

- `material` — Item type identifier
- `tag` — Unique identifier (auto-generated on create)
- `name` — Translated display name
- `lore` — Translated lore lines
- `damage` — Damage value
- `unbreakable` — Infinite durability flag
- `enchant` — Enchantment ID → level map

### Unsafe Enchantments

Enchantments are applied using `meta.add_enchant(enchant, level, True)` where `force=True`
bypasses the vanilla level cap, allowing items with extreme enchantment levels.
